    "summary": "I am an Assistant Professor Science, Business & Innovation (SBI) at the Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam. I focus on researching and valorizing natural science, social science and technology in the context of innovation processes and transitions with an overarching focus on sustainability. I teach in the SBI bachelor, master and research programs. \n\nMy research interest is in sustainable innovation in the life sciences and food sectors and I apply an institutional and systemic perspective to analyze broad societal challenges in that domain. I am currently focusing on innovation processes within the realm of planetary health.\n\nI hold a PhD in innovation sciences obtained at Utrecht University. In my dissertation I focused on the role of institutional hybridity and change in innovation processes.",
